The Philadelphia Philles placed
second baseman Freddy Galvis, who is replacing injured All-Star
Chase Utley, on the disabled list with a strained lower back,
the team said on its Twitter feed.  Galvis, 22, is batting .226 with 3 home runs and 24 runs
batted in during 58 games this year. Utley started the season on
the disabled list with injured knees.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
